    • Field Detail

      • LPSolver

        public static final StringOptionKey LPSolver
        Name of external LP implementation used to solve the linear program version of the graph.

        The following values are supported:

        ""
        Use the default, which is currently "matlab"
        "matlab"
        Only works when using Dimple from MATLAB front-end. This solver uses the LP solver configured in MATLAB, which is described by the MatlabLPSolver option.
        "CPLEX"
        "GLPK"
        "Gurobi"
        "LpSolve"
        "MiniSat"
        "Mosek"
        "SAT4J"
        The chosen solver must be separately installed and configured for use in Java.

        See Also:
        Java ILP - Java Interface to ILP Solvers

      • MatlabLPSolver

        public static final StringOptionKey MatlabLPSolver
        Name of LP solver to use in MATLAB when "matlab" is the LPSolver value.

        The following values are currently supported:

        ""
        Uses the default, which is currently "matlab"
        "matlab"
        Uses linprog function from the Optimization Toolbox
        "glpk"
        "glpkIP"
        "gurobi"
        "gurobiIP
        The chosen solver must be separately installed and configured for use in MATLAB.
